      For JENDL-2, the resonance parameters were evaluated by     5837 1451
    Kikuchi[4]. Neutron widths were obtained from data measured   5837 1451
    by Hacken et al.[5] and Camarda [6], and radiation            5837 1451
    widths from capture areas by Musgrove et al.[7] For the       5837 1451
    resonances only whose capture area was measured, the neutron  5837 1451
    width was deduced by assuming the average radiation width of  5837 1451
    0.034+-0.029 eV for s-wave resonances and 0.029+-0.008 eV for 5837 1451
    p-wave ones.  A negative resonance was added so as to         5837 1451
    reproduce the capture cross section of 0.57+-0.04 barn and    5837 1451
    the elastic scattering cross section of 2.83+-0.11 barns at   5837 1451
    0.0253 eV[8].                                                 5837 1451
